## QUESTION TEXT
The graph shows the cost of electricity with Company A. [Diagram: A line graph on a Cartesian coordinate system. The horizontal x-axis is labeled 'Electricity used (kwH)' and ranges from 0 to 250 in increments of 50. The vertical y-axis is labeled 'Cost of electricity (£)' and ranges from 0 to 35 in increments of 5. A straight line starts at the origin (0,0) and passes through the point (200, 25), indicating a linear relationship where cost is £25 for 200 kwH.]

a) Use the information in the graph to estimate the cost of electricity for a customer who uses 450 kwH of electricity.

b) Company B charges 14.3 pence per kwH of electricity used. If Company B's cost of electricity was plotted on the same axes as Company A's cost of electricity, which line would be steeper? Explain how you know.

## MARKING SCHEME
- M1: 1 kwH costs £0.125 oe soi. 
- M1: their 0.125 x 450. For the first M1 mark, costs must be from graph within +/- 1/2 small square ie £0.5[0] 
- M1: 55.5[0] to 57.[0] nfww 
- A3: "B" with 12.5 and 14.3 or 0.125 and 0.143 (Method 1: 1 mark for 12.5 or 0.125. 1 mark dep for 14.3 or 0.143 stated. 1 mark for "B" with comparison. Method 2: calculation for B and comparing with A. Mark method not accuracy for first two marks. e.g. B because 1kwH costs 12.5p which is less than Company B's charge)

Please generate a perfect model answer following the scheme.


