Vector m = (2, k) and vector n = (3, 11). Vector 2m + n is parallel to (1, -1). Find the value of k.
</span>
<div class="model_answer">
$2\mathbf{m} + \mathbf{n} = 2\begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ k \end{pmatrix} + \begin{pmatrix} 3 \\ 11 \end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix} 4 \\ 2k \end{pmatrix} + \begin{pmatrix} 3 \\ 11 \end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix} 7 \\ 2k+11 \end{pmatrix}$ <span class="marking-code">[M2]</span><br>
Since $2\mathbf{m} + \mathbf{n}$ is parallel to $\begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ -1 \end{pmatrix}$, we have $2k+11 = -7$ <span class="marking-code">[M1]</span><br>
$2k = -18$<br>
$k = -9$ <span class="marking-code">[M1]</span>
</div>
