<span class="model_question">Write as a single fraction in its simplest form. $x/(x+2) + (x+1)/(x-2) - 6x/(x²-4)$
</span>
<div class="model_answer">
$\frac{x}{x+2} + \frac{x+1}{x-2} - \frac{6x}{x^2-4}$ <br>
$=\frac{x(x-2)}{(x+2)(x-2)} + \frac{(x+1)(x+2)}{(x-2)(x+2)} - \frac{6x}{(x+2)(x-2)}$ <span class="marking-code">[M1]</span><br>
$=\frac{x(x-2) + (x+1)(x+2) - 6x}{(x+2)(x-2)}$ <span class="marking-code">[M3]</span><br>
$=\frac{x^2 - 2x + x^2 + 3x + 2 - 6x}{(x+2)(x-2)}$ <br>
$=\frac{2x^2 - 5x + 2}{(x+2)(x-2)}$ <br>
$=\frac{(2x-1)(x-2)}{(x+2)(x-2)}$ <br>
$=\frac{2x-1}{x+2}$ <span class="marking-code">[M2]</span>
</div>
